Program: Free Thinking
Title: Slavoj Zizek, Protest, Anonymous and City of Angels
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04v24sx
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 16 Dec 2014
Philosopher Slavoj Žižek speaks to Philip Dodd about the radical left, how technology and the rise of religious fundamentalism have changed his reading of Marxism, and what he sees as the failings of the protest movements he helped inspire. Douglas Carswell, Beatrix Campbell and Gabriella Coleman explore the success of protest movements from online activists and Anonymous to demonstrations on the street. Theatre critic Matt Wolf gives his first-night review of City of Angels at the Donmar Warehouse. Gabriella Coleman is the author of Hacker, Hoaxer, Whistleblower, Spy: The Many Faces of Anonymous Slavoj Žižek is author of Trouble in Paradise Producer: Georgia Catt. Editor: Robyn Read You can download this programme by searching in the Arts and Ideas podcasts for the broadcast date. Show less